Traffic in a city like Bangalore is one of the busiest not only in India but it is also one of the busiest in the world. Due to maximum number of vehicles, about 60 lakhs or 6 millions including two wheelers have made the roads difficult to commute. Parking space is one of the main problem. Therefore people tends to break rules by parking their vehicles wherever they can. The saying "everyone is so hurry to reach their destination in time but only few of them made it in time". Thus depicting how busy the traffic here in Bangalore is.
